# Indicative Quote Waterfall — EXP-20260630-007 — Agarbatti to Fiji

## RFQ facts
- Product: Agarbatti / incense sticks
- Quantity: 1 MT / 1,000 kg
- Destination: Fiji
- Buyer payment shown: T/T
- Requested shipping: FOB or CIF
- Source: go4WorldBusiness buy lead 1304702 — https://go4worldbusiness.com/inquiries/send/buyleads/1304702/wanted--agarbatti-incense-sticks

## Recommended indicative quote to buyer
Use standard export-grade agarbatti assumption until supplier quotes arrive.

| Incoterm | Quote per kg | Total for 1 MT | Use when |
|---|---:|---:|---|
| FOB India port | USD 2.25–2.35/kg | USD 2,250–2,350 | Buyer handles freight/import |
| CIF Fiji, provisional | USD 3.65–3.75/kg | USD 3,650–3,750 | You include ocean freight/insurance to Fiji |

## Recommended single-number reply if buyer wants a quick quote
- FOB India: **USD 2,300 for 1 MT**
- CIF Fiji: **USD 3,700 for 1 MT**, subject to final port, packing volume, and freight confirmation.

## Do-not-go-below floors before supplier/freight confirmation
- FOB floor: **USD 2.05/kg / USD 2,050 per MT**
- CIF floor: **USD 3.35/kg / USD 3,350 per MT**

## Planning assumptions used
- Supplier standard export-ready agarbatti: ₹115/kg planning estimate.
- Export packing: ₹18/kg.
- Inland/docs/handling: ₹22/kg.
- Planning USD/INR: 83.
- FOB cost basis: ₹155/kg ≈ USD 1.87/kg.
- Provisional Fiji LCL freight + insurance + handling buffer: USD 1,250/MT.

## Commercial terms to attach
- Validity: 7 days.
- Payment: 50% advance T/T + 50% before dispatch / against scanned BL.
- Final quote subject to fragrance, stick length, packaging, destination port, and freight confirmation.
- HSN/origin/certification to be verified before final proforma invoice.

## Source basis
- Screenshot/source RFQ details from go4WorldBusiness.
- Supplier shortlist: outputs/supplier_shortlists/EXP-20260630-007_agarbatti_fiji_supplier_shortlist.md.
- Public supplier directory snippets showed low-end basic agarbatti around ₹50–₹70/kg and broader export/premium ranges above that; this draft uses a safer standard export-grade assumption rather than the cheapest raw/basic listing.

